    <slide environment="" chapter_type="" wbtag="slide" canon_num="15" id="s15" slide="15" course="" chapter="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" chapter_title="" section_title="">
      <keywords slide="15" environ="slide" chapter="" course=""/>
      <paragraphs course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="" wbtag="paragraphs"> The achromatic channel is most responsive to
spectral light which lies in the green or yellowish-green range.  This may explain
why green and yellow spectral colors appear brighter than the rest. </paragraphs>
      <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment=""></p>
      <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="image" environment="">
        <img src="https://www.math.cuhk.edu.hk/~pschan/cranach-dev/images/Linear_visible_spectrum.svg" environment="" />
      </div>
      <hr xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="" />
      <newcol course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="newcol">
        <paragraphs course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs"> Moreover, "saturation" may now be understood as a function of the
"relative amounts of chromatic and achromatic responses."
Hence, </paragraphs>
        <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="newcol"></p>
        <blockquote xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="newcol">
          <paragraphs xmlns="http://www.math.cuhk.edu.hk/~pschan/cranach" course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs"> At the two spectral extremes where the chromatic responses are large relative to
the white response, the spectral saturation is high. </paragraphs>
        </blockquote>
        <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="text-align:right;font-size:0.75em" environment="newcol">
          <i environment="newcol">
            <paragraphs xmlns="http://www.math.cuhk.edu.hk/~pschan/cranach" course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs">An Opponent-Process Theory of Color Vision</paragraphs>
          </i>
          <paragraphs xmlns="http://www.math.cuhk.edu.hk/~pschan/cranach" course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs">, L. Hurvich, D. Jameson </paragraphs>
        </div>
        <hr xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="newcol" />
        <paragraphs course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs"> This explains the shape of the </paragraphs>
        <a xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" target="_blank" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Munsell_color_system" environment="newcol">
          <b environment="newcol">
            <paragraphs xmlns="http://www.math.cuhk.edu.hk/~pschan/cranach" course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs">Munsell Sphere</paragraphs>
          </b>
        </a>
        <paragraphs course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs">: </paragraphs>
        <br xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="newcol" />
        <collapse course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="collapse">
          <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" class="dual" environment="newcol">
            <paragraphs xmlns="http://www.math.cuhk.edu.hk/~pschan/cranach" course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs">     </paragraphs>
            <div class="dual-left" environment="newcol">
              <paragraphs xmlns="http://www.math.cuhk.edu.hk/~pschan/cranach" course="" chapter="" chapter_type="" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" environment="newcol" wbtag="paragraphs">         </paragraphs>
              <a title="Albert Henry Munsell [Public domain], via Wikimedia Commons" href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Munsell_color_sphere.png" environment="newcol">
